  "prompt": "How long does it take to open a savings bank account in ICICI bank?",
  "response": "The time it takes to open a savings bank account at ICICI Bank can vary based on a few factors, including the specific branch you visit, the completeness of your documentation, and whether any additional verification processes are needed. However, typically:\n\n1. **Online Application:**\n   - ICICI Bank offers the facility to open a savings account online. This process can be quite fast, potentially taking as little as a few minutes to complete the application. You will need to upload necessary documents and complete e-KYC (Electronic Know Your Customer) verification. If all information is correctly provided and verified, the account can be opened almost instantly.\n\n2. **In-Branch Application:**\n   - If you visit a branch to open your account, it generally takes about 30 minutes to an hour if you have all the necessary documents ready and there are no issues with verification. You may need to fill out forms, submit your documents, and wait for the staff to process your request. If additional verification is required or if there is high foot traffic at the branch, it might take longer.\n\n### Required Documents:\nEnsure you have the following documents ready to avoid delays:\n- Proof of Identity (like Aadhaar Card, Passport, Voter ID)\n- Proof of Address (like Aadhaar Card, Passport, Utility Bills)\n- PAN Card (Permanent Account Number) or Form 60 if you don\u2019t have a PAN Card\n- Passport-sized photographs\n\n### Summary:\n- **Online Application:** A few minutes to a couple of hours (if e-KYC is flawless)\n- **In-Branch Application:** 30 minutes to a few hours\n\nIt's advisable to check ICICI Bank's official website or contact customer service for the most accurate and up-to-date information regarding the account opening process.",
